        <item>
      <title>Nature&#8217;s Simplicity</title>
      <link>https://minimalissimo.com/moods/natures-simplicity</link>
      <guid>moods/natures-simplicity</guid>
      <pubDate>Wed, 29 Jul 2020 00:00:00 +0200</pubDate>
      <description><![CDATA[<p>Simple shapes, natural materials, and warm colours feature in this collaboration between artist <a href="https://eloisa.studio" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Eloisa Iturbe</a> and designers <a href="https://www.estudio-diario.com/en/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Estudio Diario</a> to create a series of sunlit images. A selection of everyday pieces were set amidst a landscape of beautiful geometric shapes and photographed under the light of the midday sun by Eloisa.</p><img alt="" src="https://minimalissimo.com/content/moods/65_natures-simplicity/container.jpg"><img alt="" src="https://minimalissimo.com/content/moods/65_natures-simplicity/hangers_1.jpg"><img alt="" src="https://minimalissimo.com/content/moods/65_natures-simplicity/hangers_3.jpg"><img alt="" src="https://minimalissimo.com/content/moods/65_natures-simplicity/poetic-forms_3.jpg"><img alt="" src="https://minimalissimo.com/content/moods/65_natures-simplicity/salvaje_bandeja-cepillo.jpg"><img alt="" src="https://minimalissimo.com/content/moods/65_natures-simplicity/salvaje_espejo.jpg"><img alt="" src="https://minimalissimo.com/content/moods/65_natures-simplicity/table_3.jpg"><img alt="" src="https://minimalissimo.com/content/moods/65_natures-simplicity/wall-clock_1.jpg"><img alt="" src="https://minimalissimo.com/content/moods/65_natures-simplicity/wall-clock_2.jpg">]]></description>
    </item>
        <item>
      <title>Matthew Hilton</title>
      <link>https://minimalissimo.com/creators/matthew-hilton</link>
      <guid>creators/matthew-hilton</guid>
      <pubDate>Mon, 27 Jul 2020 00:00:00 +0200</pubDate>
      <description><![CDATA[<figure class="img-figure"><div class="img-wrapper" data-orientation="landscape" style="padding-bottom: 66.642857142857%"><img alt="Matthew Hilton Portrait" class="img" data-original="100w" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 446px) 402px, (max-width: 600px) 504px, 702px" src="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-portrait.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60" srcset="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-portrait.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60 402w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-portrait.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60 504w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-portrait.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60 702w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-portrait.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 804w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-portrait.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1008w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-portrait.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1404w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-portrait.jpg?q=60"></div></figure>
<blockquote>
<p>I like simple quality which works well and lasts. Things don’t even need to be beautiful, just not ugly. It seems so easy and obvious to me and yet it is hard to find products which fulfil those criteria.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>As one is apt to do when preparing questions for someone as talented as British furniture designer <a href="https://matthewhilton.com" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Matthew Hilton</a>, I have spent a considerable amount of time studying his work for such storied brands like De La Espada, DWR, and Case Furniture. At every turn, I find reasons to be in awe of his flexibility and clear understanding of form and function, leaving little doubt as to why, in 2004, he was elected the highest honour a British designer can receive: Royal Designer for Industry (RDI) by the Royal Society of Arts (RSA). That was over 16 years ago and Matthew Hilton shows no signs of slowing down. His new studio presents projects that look primed to influence designers well past the 21st century.</p>
<p>Whether working on his own or now with a small collective of forward thinking designers at his eponymous studio, Matthew Hilton’s insights on design will undoubtedly be worthwhile reading. In this interview, we push beyond the boundaries of furniture design. There are insights on marketing vs. making, visual consumption, and the importance of historic design.</p>
<figure class="img-figure"><div class="img-wrapper" data-orientation="landscape" style="padding-bottom: 66.666666666667%"><img alt="Matthew Hilton Studio" class="img" data-original="100w" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 446px) 402px, (max-width: 600px) 504px, 702px" src="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-5.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60" srcset="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-5.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60 402w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-5.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60 504w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-5.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60 702w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-5.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 804w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-5.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1008w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-5.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1404w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-5.jpg?q=60"></div></figure>
<figure class="img-figure"><div class="img-wrapper" data-orientation="landscape" style="padding-bottom: 66.666666666667%"><img alt="Matthew Hilton Studio" class="img" data-original="100w" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 446px) 402px, (max-width: 600px) 504px, 702px" src="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-6.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60" srcset="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-6.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60 402w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-6.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60 504w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-6.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60 702w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-6.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 804w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-6.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1008w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-6.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1404w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-6.jpg?q=60"></div></figure>
<div class="question"><p>How would you describe the origin of your design ethos?</p></div>
<p>My design school, Kingston Polytechnic in London, was steeped in quite strict modernist Bauhaus design theory. Geometric design and “Less is more”. I am in tune with a lot of that thinking, but I have also always been interested in softer organic forms with restraint and subtlety. There’s an aesthetic balance between the organic and the geometric, a point, which is different for everyone I suppose, but when you achieve that point it’s like catching a wave, or cornering fast on a track in a car or listening to some music that properly connects—theres a thrill and excitement mixed with calm and contentment.</p>
<p>If you think of the things people regard as great design they are not usually quiet ordinary things, they are often brave and different to what was the norm of the time, but producing those things takes courage and we are often afraid of taking the risk.</p>
<div class="question"><p>Who has inspired your approach to design over the years?</p></div>
<p>So many people and things. I admire people who have a strong ethos, people who stick to who they are, whether that means they try lots of different things and work in many different areas, or they spend their life making monochromatic stripe paintings, or perfecting making bread, it is natural to that person and they do it without compromise.</p>
<figure class="img-figure"><div class="img-wrapper" data-orientation="landscape" style="padding-bottom: 66.666666666667%"><img alt="Matthew Hilton Studio" class="img" data-original="100w" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 446px) 402px, (max-width: 600px) 504px, 702px" src="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-14.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60" srcset="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-14.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60 402w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-14.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60 504w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-14.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60 702w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-14.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 804w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-14.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1008w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-14.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1404w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-14.jpg?q=60"></div></figure>
<figure class="img-figure"><div class="img-wrapper" data-orientation="landscape" style="padding-bottom: 66.666666666667%"><img alt="Matthew Hilton Studio" class="img" data-original="100w" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 446px) 402px, (max-width: 600px) 504px, 702px" src="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-12.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60" srcset="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-12.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60 402w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-12.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60 504w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-12.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60 702w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-12.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 804w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-12.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1008w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-12.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1404w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-12.jpg?q=60"></div></figure>
<figure class="img-figure"><div class="img-wrapper" data-orientation="landscape" style="padding-bottom: 66.666666666667%"><img alt="Matthew Hilton Studio" class="img" data-original="100w" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 446px) 402px, (max-width: 600px) 504px, 702px" src="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-13.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60" srcset="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-13.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60 402w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-13.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60 504w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-13.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60 702w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-13.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 804w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-13.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1008w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-13.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1404w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-13.jpg?q=60"></div></figure>
<div class="question"><p>Your creative journey seems so rich. You even dabbled with fashion design, thanks to David Bowie. What motivates you to explore other areas of design?</p></div>
<p>I think it is partly a function of being a bit obsessional, and a bit of a dreamer and a need to make things. I have always made stuff, or altered things I bought so that they suited me better. I realise that my interests haven’t changed much fundamentally over my lifetime and I still experience the same frustration of not being able to find the things I want to own. There is a camera I want but it doesn’t quite exist, there is car in my imagination, a hi fi, art for my walls, carpets, sculpture, and many other things. I am a maker and if I am desiring something I start to imagine what that thing would be like.</p>
<p>I want things to be well made, the best they can be and I don’t have the skills to make them myself. Designing and working with companies who produce really well is a way for me to own the things I want. Why are cameras for example getting so much more complicated and harder to use? It drives me mad. Computers were like that before Apple, and major camera manufacturers have not learnt much from that industry.</p>
<div class="question"><p>There is a clear respect for classic designs in your work, like with your Windsor and Ando chairs. You also seem to have a grasp on the potency of function. How have you managed to blend these two influences together?</p></div>
<p>I dislike things which don’t work properly, are over complicated, and have illogical ways of operating. I like simple quality which works well and lasts. Things don’t even need to be beautiful, just not ugly. It seems so easy and obvious to me and yet it is hard to find products which fulfil those criteria.</p>
<figure class="img-figure"><div class="img-wrapper" data-orientation="landscape" style="padding-bottom: 66.666666666667%"><img alt="Matthew Hilton Studio" class="img" data-original="100w" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 446px) 402px, (max-width: 600px) 504px, 702px" src="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-1.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60" srcset="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-1.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60 402w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-1.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60 504w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-1.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60 702w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-1.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 804w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-1.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1008w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-1.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1404w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-1.jpg?q=60"></div></figure>
<figure class="img-figure"><div class="img-wrapper" data-orientation="landscape" style="padding-bottom: 66.666666666667%"><img alt="Matthew Hilton Studio" class="img" data-original="100w" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 446px) 402px, (max-width: 600px) 504px, 702px" src="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-2.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60" srcset="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-2.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60 402w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-2.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60 504w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-2.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60 702w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-2.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 804w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-2.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1008w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-2.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1404w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-2.jpg?q=60"></div></figure>
<div class="question"><p>What can designers learn from history?</p></div>
<p>Almost everything. Understanding what has worked well in the past and the reason why is the best foundation for success in the present and future, in all kinds of senses, in life in general, in design, in everything. The past is important, it helps us form the future. But I do not want to reproduce the past. I want make new things. Sometimes I find I just have so much respect for the ingenuity or creativity visible in an object I want to use that as a point to start something new, something which advances that attitude, or evolves the thinking because we have new techniques or ways of living that have changed.</p>
<div class="question"><p>You’ve collaborated with some of the most well-respected brands in modern furniture design like DWR and De La Espada. What makes a good collaboration work?</p></div>
<p>A good collaboration is about people, as with everything, the company is a construct of the people who own it and work in it. Each brand has its own DNA made up of the people, the resources they have, and the way they use those resources. Some companies own a factory and employ skilled makers, others use factories all over the world without owning them, there are pros and cons to each way of producing.</p>
<p>Organisation of the process has to be tight and focussed and also allow for creative freedom. The development team and the makers and the management all need to have respect and trust in the process and each other whilst pushing possibilities into new areas, and moving things on. There needs to be a true appreciation of design and aesthetics, a real understanding of the manufacturing challenges and a realistic attitude to business. People need to be creative and pragmatic, be able to compromise to find the best possible balance, and it takes perseverance and conviction in our ability to find a way.</p>
<figure class="img-figure"><div class="img-wrapper" data-orientation="landscape" style="padding-bottom: 66.666666666667%"><img alt="Matthew Hilton Studio" class="img" data-original="100w" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 446px) 402px, (max-width: 600px) 504px, 702px" src="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-4.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60" srcset="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-4.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60 402w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-4.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60 504w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-4.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60 702w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-4.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 804w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-4.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1008w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-4.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1404w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-4.jpg?q=60"></div></figure>
<figure class="img-figure"><div class="img-wrapper" data-orientation="landscape" style="padding-bottom: 66.666666666667%"><img alt="Matthew Hilton Studio" class="img" data-original="100w" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 446px) 402px, (max-width: 600px) 504px, 702px" src="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-9.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60" srcset="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-9.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60 402w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-9.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60 504w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-9.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60 702w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-9.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 804w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-9.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1008w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-9.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1404w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-9.jpg?q=60"></div></figure>
<div class="question"><p>Has working consistently with a small team of designers within your current studio changed how you work?</p></div>
<p>Apart from a short time at Habitat UK when I was head of a team of perhaps six people, my own studio has never employed more than two designers, so I have always worked with a small team.</p>
<p>I think and hope that all that has happened is that I have got better at working in a team as I get older. I have to be able to focus on different aspects of the business through the day. Running the studio as a business like any other, watching cash, arranging loans, paying tax and wages, and also discussing the finer detail of a joint in a chair with my two designers. I have to accept that I cannot do everything and other people are better in some areas than me, and I need to allow people to properly contribute. Learning all this and really absorbing it into my work life has at times been tough but in the end it has led to a place of far more freedom in lots of ways.</p>
<div class="question"><p>Bowie once said, “Turn and face the strange changes.” Social media seems like one of those strange changes. Is it having a positive effect on modern design?</p></div>
<p>Its effect is stronger on the marketing of design products I think. It does not influence the way I design things at all, it effects how finished designs are seen and sold. Perhaps trends move faster. Images of products are far more important than ever before, the retail part of the design business always felt that people would want to touch, feel, sit, and try furniture, but that has been changing slowly for years. I hear reports of online sales growing by 80% in the three months of UK lockdown, showroom sales would have been zero so it is a distortion but as with a lot of things the (Covid-19) virus has accelerated shifts in society which were already happening.</p>
<figure class="img-figure"><div class="img-wrapper" data-orientation="landscape" style="padding-bottom: 66.694915254237%"><img alt="Matthew Hilton Studio" class="img" data-original="100w" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 446px) 402px, (max-width: 600px) 504px, 702px" src="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-7.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60" srcset="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-7.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60 402w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-7.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60 504w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-7.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60 702w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-7.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 804w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-7.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1008w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-7.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1404w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-7.jpg?q=60"></div></figure>
<figure class="img-figure"><div class="img-wrapper" data-orientation="landscape" style="padding-bottom: 66.694915254237%"><img alt="Matthew Hilton Studio" class="img" data-original="100w" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 446px) 402px, (max-width: 600px) 504px, 702px" src="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-8.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60" srcset="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-8.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60 402w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-8.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60 504w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-8.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60 702w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-8.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 804w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-8.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1008w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-8.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1404w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-8.jpg?q=60"></div></figure>
<div class="question"><p>It does appear that we are living in an age where products appear to be designed simply for immediate visual consumption. Why is this a disservice?</p></div>
<p>I think this appears to be the case and is a real phenomena but I believe that there is still demand for properly designed product which is well made, functions well, and lasts aesthetically. Flicking through images and superficially liking is entertainment and does influence purchases but in the end people have to decide if they will buy the new dining table or not, and I think that parting with significant amounts of money to own something focusses peoples minds and they then make decisions based on their circumstances and needs not solely on pretty images.</p>
<div class="question"><p>Looking back at your catalogue, what projects stand out to you?</p></div>
<p>I am lucky to feel proud of a number of pieces, they will be obvious to most people because people recognise when something has the right balance and when things work. I am proudest of the things where the risks paid off. Things that have presence and which people have genuine feelings about, whether that is love or hate.</p>
<p>I want to make beautiful things. That is not superficial, it isn’t pretty, it isn’t to do with a trend or a style, a colour, or a material. Instead, it’s in the objects bones, in its guts. It belongs to now or a little while in the future or it is timeless. I find it near impossible to describe and it takes real work to get there and the people we work with have to trust and invest. Making things which do this is not something that happens all the time, there are too many ingredients which need to be balanced, but when it does, you get a thing, an object, a product which has lasting beauty. There is no formula to achieving that.</p>
<div class="question"><p>What does a day off look like for you?</p></div>
<p>I don’t do much on days off. I rest. I can spend a whole day listening to music and maybe sketching a bit. I want time with my son and or my girlfriend, a short walk out for a coffee, perhaps a good healthy lunch somewhere, some gym time, or a lunch at home with friends and wine, a walk and a sleep. I also like going to galleries and watching films.</p>
<div class="question"><p>What would you like your legacy to be?</p></div>
<p>I don’t really think about this apart from in practical terms of liking my designs to be long lasting and valued.</p>
<figure class="img-figure"><div class="img-wrapper" data-orientation="landscape" style="padding-bottom: 66.666666666667%"><img alt="Matthew Hilton Studio" class="img" data-original="100w" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 446px) 402px, (max-width: 600px) 504px, 702px" src="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-11.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60" srcset="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-11.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60 402w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-11.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60 504w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-11.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60 702w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-11.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 804w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-11.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1008w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-11.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1404w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-11.jpg?q=60"></div></figure>
<figure class="img-figure"><div class="img-wrapper" data-orientation="landscape" style="padding-bottom: 66.666666666667%"><img alt="Matthew Hilton Studio" class="img" data-original="100w" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 446px) 402px, (max-width: 600px) 504px, 702px" src="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-10.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60" srcset="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-10.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60 402w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-10.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60 504w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-10.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60 702w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-10.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 804w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-10.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1008w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-10.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1404w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/creators/32_matthew-hilton/matthew-hilton-10.jpg?q=60"></div></figure>]]></description>
    </item>
        <item>
      <title>Opper Lounge Chair</title>
      <link>https://minimalissimo.com/articles/opper-lounge-chair</link>
      <guid>articles/opper-lounge-chair</guid>
      <pubDate>Wed, 22 Jul 2020 00:00:00 +0200</pubDate>
      <description><![CDATA[<figure class="img-figure"><div class="img-wrapper" data-orientation="landscape" style="padding-bottom: 66.7%"><img alt="Opper Lounge Chair" class="img" data-original="100w" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 446px) 402px, (max-width: 600px) 504px, 702px" src="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/185_opper-lounge-chair/gregoire-de-lafforest-meridienne-opper-01.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60" srcset="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/185_opper-lounge-chair/gregoire-de-lafforest-meridienne-opper-01.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60 402w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/185_opper-lounge-chair/gregoire-de-lafforest-meridienne-opper-01.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60 504w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/185_opper-lounge-chair/gregoire-de-lafforest-meridienne-opper-01.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60 702w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/185_opper-lounge-chair/gregoire-de-lafforest-meridienne-opper-01.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 804w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/185_opper-lounge-chair/gregoire-de-lafforest-meridienne-opper-01.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1008w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/185_opper-lounge-chair/gregoire-de-lafforest-meridienne-opper-01.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1404w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/185_opper-lounge-chair/gregoire-de-lafforest-meridienne-opper-01.jpg?q=60"></div></figure>
<p>What do we look for in a lounge chair? First, the beauty. Is the design aesthetic? Then the materials. How is it made? How does it feel? How long will it last? Then we have the all important function. Does it work well? Is it comfortable? Is it simple to use? These may seem like pretty simple questions, but answering them through a design language is always a challenge. A challenge that French designer <a href="http://www.gregoiredelafforest.com/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Gr&eacute;goire de Lafforest</a> overcame with one of his latest offerings.</p>
<figure class="img-figure"><div class="img-wrapper" data-orientation="landscape" style="padding-bottom: 66.7%"><img alt="Opper Lounge Chair" class="img" data-original="100w" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 446px) 402px, (max-width: 600px) 504px, 702px" src="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/185_opper-lounge-chair/gregoire-de-lafforest-meridienne-opper-03.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60" srcset="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/185_opper-lounge-chair/gregoire-de-lafforest-meridienne-opper-03.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60 402w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/185_opper-lounge-chair/gregoire-de-lafforest-meridienne-opper-03.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60 504w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/185_opper-lounge-chair/gregoire-de-lafforest-meridienne-opper-03.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60 702w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/185_opper-lounge-chair/gregoire-de-lafforest-meridienne-opper-03.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 804w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/185_opper-lounge-chair/gregoire-de-lafforest-meridienne-opper-03.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1008w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/185_opper-lounge-chair/gregoire-de-lafforest-meridienne-opper-03.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1404w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/185_opper-lounge-chair/gregoire-de-lafforest-meridienne-opper-03.jpg?q=60"></div></figure>
<figure class="img-figure"><div class="img-wrapper" data-orientation="landscape" style="padding-bottom: 66.7%"><img alt="Opper Lounge Chair" class="img" data-original="100w" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 446px) 402px, (max-width: 600px) 504px, 702px" src="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/185_opper-lounge-chair/gregoire-de-lafforest-meridienne-opper-02.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60" srcset="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/185_opper-lounge-chair/gregoire-de-lafforest-meridienne-opper-02.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60 402w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/185_opper-lounge-chair/gregoire-de-lafforest-meridienne-opper-02.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60 504w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/185_opper-lounge-chair/gregoire-de-lafforest-meridienne-opper-02.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60 702w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/185_opper-lounge-chair/gregoire-de-lafforest-meridienne-opper-02.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 804w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/185_opper-lounge-chair/gregoire-de-lafforest-meridienne-opper-02.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1008w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/185_opper-lounge-chair/gregoire-de-lafforest-meridienne-opper-02.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1404w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/185_opper-lounge-chair/gregoire-de-lafforest-meridienne-opper-02.jpg?q=60"></div></figure>
<p>The design of the Opper lounge chair is based on the notion of balance between weights and lines. It is a play of contrasts between the lightweight seat and the raw strength and heaviness of the Carrara marble plinth, and between the hard coldness of marble and the warm softness of leather. These two very different elements come together through a play of symmetry of the curves creating a large backrest at the seat and a tablet in the continuity of the base.</p>
<p>To contrast with the curves of the seat and create tension in the shape, the central axis of the seat is highlighted by the changes in materials. The overall appearance of the lounge chair is clean and precise, but comfort is not forgotten. With a set of foams of different densities, comfort is optimal and contrasts with the visual impression of stiffness.</p>
<figure class="img-figure"><div class="img-wrapper" data-orientation="landscape" style="padding-bottom: 66.7%"><img alt="Opper Lounge Chair" class="img" data-original="100w" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 446px) 402px, (max-width: 600px) 504px, 702px" src="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/185_opper-lounge-chair/gregoire-de-lafforest-meridienne-opper-06.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60" srcset="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/185_opper-lounge-chair/gregoire-de-lafforest-meridienne-opper-06.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60 402w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/185_opper-lounge-chair/gregoire-de-lafforest-meridienne-opper-06.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60 504w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/185_opper-lounge-chair/gregoire-de-lafforest-meridienne-opper-06.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60 702w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/185_opper-lounge-chair/gregoire-de-lafforest-meridienne-opper-06.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 804w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/185_opper-lounge-chair/gregoire-de-lafforest-meridienne-opper-06.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1008w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/185_opper-lounge-chair/gregoire-de-lafforest-meridienne-opper-06.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1404w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/185_opper-lounge-chair/gregoire-de-lafforest-meridienne-opper-06.jpg?q=60"></div></figure>
<figure class="img-figure"><div class="img-wrapper" data-orientation="landscape" style="padding-bottom: 66.6%"><img alt="Opper Lounge Chair" class="img" data-original="100w" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 446px) 402px, (max-width: 600px) 504px, 702px" src="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/185_opper-lounge-chair/gregoire-de-lafforest-meridienne-opper-09.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60" srcset="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/185_opper-lounge-chair/gregoire-de-lafforest-meridienne-opper-09.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60 402w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/185_opper-lounge-chair/gregoire-de-lafforest-meridienne-opper-09.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60 504w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/185_opper-lounge-chair/gregoire-de-lafforest-meridienne-opper-09.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60 702w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/185_opper-lounge-chair/gregoire-de-lafforest-meridienne-opper-09.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 804w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/185_opper-lounge-chair/gregoire-de-lafforest-meridienne-opper-09.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1008w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/185_opper-lounge-chair/gregoire-de-lafforest-meridienne-opper-09.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1404w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/185_opper-lounge-chair/gregoire-de-lafforest-meridienne-opper-09.jpg?q=60"></div></figure>
<figure class="img-figure"><div class="img-wrapper" data-orientation="landscape" style="padding-bottom: 66.7%"><img alt="Opper Lounge Chair" class="img" data-original="100w" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 446px) 402px, (max-width: 600px) 504px, 702px" src="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/185_opper-lounge-chair/gregoire-de-lafforest-meridienne-opper-04.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60" srcset="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/185_opper-lounge-chair/gregoire-de-lafforest-meridienne-opper-04.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60 402w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/185_opper-lounge-chair/gregoire-de-lafforest-meridienne-opper-04.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60 504w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/185_opper-lounge-chair/gregoire-de-lafforest-meridienne-opper-04.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60 702w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/185_opper-lounge-chair/gregoire-de-lafforest-meridienne-opper-04.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 804w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/185_opper-lounge-chair/gregoire-de-lafforest-meridienne-opper-04.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1008w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/185_opper-lounge-chair/gregoire-de-lafforest-meridienne-opper-04.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1404w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/185_opper-lounge-chair/gregoire-de-lafforest-meridienne-opper-04.jpg?q=60"></div></figure>
<p>Inspired by the motorcycle saddles of the 70s, the quilted seat brings an impression of comfort and a refined aesthetic. The marble base gives the impression of a raw solid block but by going around the back we discover, as you would behind a theatre set, that it is hollowed out and allows one to store a set of three cushions or indeed blankets if you prefer. The chair is the alliance between contemporary design and traditional materials. A mixture of tradition and modernity.</p>
<figure class="img-figure"><div class="img-wrapper" data-orientation="landscape" style="padding-bottom: 66.7%"><img alt="Opper Lounge Chair" class="img" data-original="100w" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 446px) 402px, (max-width: 600px) 504px, 702px" src="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/185_opper-lounge-chair/gregoire-de-lafforest-meridienne-opper-08.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60" srcset="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/185_opper-lounge-chair/gregoire-de-lafforest-meridienne-opper-08.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60 402w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/185_opper-lounge-chair/gregoire-de-lafforest-meridienne-opper-08.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60 504w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/185_opper-lounge-chair/gregoire-de-lafforest-meridienne-opper-08.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60 702w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/185_opper-lounge-chair/gregoire-de-lafforest-meridienne-opper-08.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 804w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/185_opper-lounge-chair/gregoire-de-lafforest-meridienne-opper-08.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1008w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/185_opper-lounge-chair/gregoire-de-lafforest-meridienne-opper-08.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1404w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/185_opper-lounge-chair/gregoire-de-lafforest-meridienne-opper-08.jpg?q=60"></div></figure>
<figure class="img-figure"><div class="img-wrapper" data-orientation="landscape" style="padding-bottom: 66.7%"><img alt="Opper Lounge Chair" class="img" data-original="100w" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 446px) 402px, (max-width: 600px) 504px, 702px" src="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/185_opper-lounge-chair/gregoire-de-lafforest-meridienne-opper-10.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60" srcset="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/185_opper-lounge-chair/gregoire-de-lafforest-meridienne-opper-10.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60 402w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/185_opper-lounge-chair/gregoire-de-lafforest-meridienne-opper-10.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60 504w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/185_opper-lounge-chair/gregoire-de-lafforest-meridienne-opper-10.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60 702w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/185_opper-lounge-chair/gregoire-de-lafforest-meridienne-opper-10.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 804w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/185_opper-lounge-chair/gregoire-de-lafforest-meridienne-opper-10.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1008w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/185_opper-lounge-chair/gregoire-de-lafforest-meridienne-opper-10.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1404w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/185_opper-lounge-chair/gregoire-de-lafforest-meridienne-opper-10.jpg?q=60"></div></figure>
<p>A trained architect and designer, Grégoire de Lafforest’s work has seen him build a portfolio of furniture and accessories that exude simplicity through soft geometries and neutral palettes. Grégoire has a well established relationship with Hermès where he contributed to the design of its head office in Paris, and continues to design furniture for their collections.</p>
<p>At the same time, he is developing his own interior architecture and furniture projects which have earned him multiple awards and recognised as a “Talent de l’élégance” award at the <em>Sommet du Luxe et de la Création</em>.</p>]]></description>
    </item>
        <item>
      <title>Rybalsky Apartment</title>
      <link>https://minimalissimo.com/articles/rybalsky-apartment</link>
      <guid>articles/rybalsky-apartment</guid>
      <pubDate>Mon, 20 Jul 2020 00:00:00 +0200</pubDate>
      <description><![CDATA[<figure class="img-figure"><div class="img-wrapper" data-orientation="landscape" style="padding-bottom: 66.666666666667%"><img alt="Rybalsky Apartment" class="img" data-original="100w" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 446px) 402px, (max-width: 600px) 504px, 702px" src="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/184_rybalsky-apartment/fild-interior-1.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60" srcset="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/184_rybalsky-apartment/fild-interior-1.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60 402w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/184_rybalsky-apartment/fild-interior-1.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60 504w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/184_rybalsky-apartment/fild-interior-1.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60 702w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/184_rybalsky-apartment/fild-interior-1.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 804w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/184_rybalsky-apartment/fild-interior-1.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1008w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/184_rybalsky-apartment/fild-interior-1.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1404w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/184_rybalsky-apartment/fild-interior-1.jpg?q=60"></div></figure>
<p>Ukrainian design duo of Dan Vakhrameyev and Kateryna Vakhrameyeva of studio <a href="http://www.thefild.com/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">FILD</a>, whose work you may already be familiar with through their lighting and furniture project <a href="https://minimalissimo.com/articles/blt-collection">BLT</a>, have unveiled their latest design. This time an interior project named, Rybalsky Apartment.</p>
<p>The goal was to create a spacious and uncluttered interior reflecting the owner’s spirit in a unique, timeless appearance while applying minimalist principles to the design.</p>
<figure class="img-figure"><div class="img-wrapper" data-orientation="portrait" style="padding-bottom: 150%"><img alt="Rybalsky Apartment" class="img" data-original="100w" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 446px) 402px, (max-width: 600px) 336px , 468px" src="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/184_rybalsky-apartment/fild-interior-2.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60" srcset="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/184_rybalsky-apartment/fild-interior-2.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60 402w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/184_rybalsky-apartment/fild-interior-2.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60 504w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/184_rybalsky-apartment/fild-interior-2.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60 702w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/184_rybalsky-apartment/fild-interior-2.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 804w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/184_rybalsky-apartment/fild-interior-2.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1008w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/184_rybalsky-apartment/fild-interior-2.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1404w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/184_rybalsky-apartment/fild-interior-2.jpg?q=60"></div></figure>
<figure class="img-figure"><div class="img-wrapper" data-orientation="landscape" style="padding-bottom: 66.666666666667%"><img alt="Rybalsky Apartment" class="img" data-original="100w" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 446px) 402px, (max-width: 600px) 504px, 702px" src="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/184_rybalsky-apartment/fild-interior-5.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60" srcset="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/184_rybalsky-apartment/fild-interior-5.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60 402w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/184_rybalsky-apartment/fild-interior-5.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60 504w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/184_rybalsky-apartment/fild-interior-5.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60 702w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/184_rybalsky-apartment/fild-interior-5.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 804w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/184_rybalsky-apartment/fild-interior-5.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1008w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/184_rybalsky-apartment/fild-interior-5.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1404w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/184_rybalsky-apartment/fild-interior-5.jpg?q=60"></div></figure>
<p>The well-combined materials, patterns, and textures create an attractive and mature perception of the dwelling. The general mood of the apartment reflects a modern, sophisticated, and tranquil space, strengthened by a restrained colour palette. The space feels like a small sanctuary where one can relax, focus, and find comfort in the simplicity of the interior.</p>
<p>The main area consists of a casual lounge zone, a dining area, an open kitchen, and two separate terrace entrances. A geometric built-in multifunction sofa unit was customised by a local furniture company based on his Dan’s sketches. The double-sided framework provides one with a joyful and practical ability to enter the kitchen without ever leaving the sofa.</p>
<figure class="img-figure"><div class="img-wrapper" data-orientation="portrait" style="padding-bottom: 150%"><img alt="Rybalsky Apartment" class="img" data-original="100w" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 446px) 402px, (max-width: 600px) 336px , 468px" src="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/184_rybalsky-apartment/fild-interior-4.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60" srcset="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/184_rybalsky-apartment/fild-interior-4.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60 402w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/184_rybalsky-apartment/fild-interior-4.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60 504w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/184_rybalsky-apartment/fild-interior-4.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60 702w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/184_rybalsky-apartment/fild-interior-4.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 804w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/184_rybalsky-apartment/fild-interior-4.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1008w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/184_rybalsky-apartment/fild-interior-4.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1404w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/184_rybalsky-apartment/fild-interior-4.jpg?q=60"></div></figure>
<figure class="img-figure"><div class="img-wrapper" data-orientation="landscape" style="padding-bottom: 66.666666666667%"><img alt="Rybalsky Apartment" class="img" data-original="100w" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 446px) 402px, (max-width: 600px) 504px, 702px" src="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/184_rybalsky-apartment/fild-interior-6.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60" srcset="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/184_rybalsky-apartment/fild-interior-6.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60 402w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/184_rybalsky-apartment/fild-interior-6.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60 504w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/184_rybalsky-apartment/fild-interior-6.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60 702w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/184_rybalsky-apartment/fild-interior-6.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 804w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/184_rybalsky-apartment/fild-interior-6.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1008w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/184_rybalsky-apartment/fild-interior-6.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1404w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/184_rybalsky-apartment/fild-interior-6.jpg?q=60"></div></figure>
<p>The black kitchen block, made from matt-black FENIX NTM, creates a perfect accent in the apartment. Furniture facades from the kitchen to wardrobe illustrate one single line linking together the apartment layout plan. Standard kitchen cabinets were intentionally removed from the design composition to emphasise the lightness of the entire furniture set.</p>
<p>In fact, all furniture elements, along with the 7 metre-long solid wardrobe structure, enliven the airiness principle as an essential design concept of the original project.</p>
<figure class="img-figure"><div class="img-wrapper" data-orientation="portrait" style="padding-bottom: 150%"><img alt="Rybalsky Apartment" class="img" data-original="100w" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 446px) 402px, (max-width: 600px) 336px , 468px" src="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/184_rybalsky-apartment/fild-interior-3.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60" srcset="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/184_rybalsky-apartment/fild-interior-3.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60 402w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/184_rybalsky-apartment/fild-interior-3.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60 504w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/184_rybalsky-apartment/fild-interior-3.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60 702w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/184_rybalsky-apartment/fild-interior-3.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 804w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/184_rybalsky-apartment/fild-interior-3.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1008w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/184_rybalsky-apartment/fild-interior-3.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1404w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/184_rybalsky-apartment/fild-interior-3.jpg?q=60"></div></figure>
<figure class="img-figure"><div class="img-wrapper" data-orientation="portrait" style="padding-bottom: 150%"><img alt="Rybalsky Apartment" class="img" data-original="100w" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 446px) 402px, (max-width: 600px) 336px , 468px" src="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/184_rybalsky-apartment/fild-interior-7.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60" srcset="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/184_rybalsky-apartment/fild-interior-7.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60 402w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/184_rybalsky-apartment/fild-interior-7.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60 504w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/184_rybalsky-apartment/fild-interior-7.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60 702w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/184_rybalsky-apartment/fild-interior-7.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 804w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/184_rybalsky-apartment/fild-interior-7.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1008w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/184_rybalsky-apartment/fild-interior-7.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1404w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/184_rybalsky-apartment/fild-interior-7.jpg?q=60"></div></figure>
<figure class="img-figure"><div class="img-wrapper" data-orientation="portrait" style="padding-bottom: 150%"><img alt="Rybalsky Apartment" class="img" data-original="100w" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 446px) 402px, (max-width: 600px) 336px , 468px" src="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/184_rybalsky-apartment/fild-interior-8.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60" srcset="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/184_rybalsky-apartment/fild-interior-8.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60 402w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/184_rybalsky-apartment/fild-interior-8.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60 504w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/184_rybalsky-apartment/fild-interior-8.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60 702w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/184_rybalsky-apartment/fild-interior-8.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 804w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/184_rybalsky-apartment/fild-interior-8.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1008w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/184_rybalsky-apartment/fild-interior-8.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1404w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/184_rybalsky-apartment/fild-interior-8.jpg?q=60"></div></figure>
<p>A discerning viewer will easily notice that adjacent walls, floor abutments, and furniture have a common element: a shadow gap, which demonstrates a fundamental minimalist approach that distinguishes the overall forms.</p>
<p>Taking centre stage however, is the partially glazed solid tile bathroom. It’s displayed as a standalone cube levitating above the general floor level and separating the main area and the master bedroom. Cleverly inserted glass breaks up the solid walls, and allows a visually open connection while keeping noise to a minimum. Water repellent fabric drapes can be adjusted with a remote control.</p>
<p>Rybalsky Apartment offers a well-balanced interior and with its soft tones of grey tints in combination with genial dimmed brown oak shades deliver a subtle perception of a restful mood.</p>]]></description>
    </item>
        <item>
      <title>Fronzoni '64 Lounge Chair</title>
      <link>https://minimalissimo.com/articles/fronzoni-64-lounge-chair</link>
      <guid>articles/fronzoni-64-lounge-chair</guid>
      <pubDate>Fri, 17 Jul 2020 00:00:00 +0200</pubDate>
      <description><![CDATA[<figure class="img-figure"><div class="img-wrapper" data-orientation="landscape" style="padding-bottom: 66.666666666667%"><img alt="Fronzoni 64 Lounge Chair" class="img" data-original="100w" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 446px) 402px, (max-width: 600px) 504px, 702px" src="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/183_fronzoni-64-lounge-chair/fronzoni-lounge-chair-1.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60" srcset="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/183_fronzoni-64-lounge-chair/fronzoni-lounge-chair-1.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60 402w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/183_fronzoni-64-lounge-chair/fronzoni-lounge-chair-1.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60 504w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/183_fronzoni-64-lounge-chair/fronzoni-lounge-chair-1.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60 702w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/183_fronzoni-64-lounge-chair/fronzoni-lounge-chair-1.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 804w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/183_fronzoni-64-lounge-chair/fronzoni-lounge-chair-1.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1008w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/183_fronzoni-64-lounge-chair/fronzoni-lounge-chair-1.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1404w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/183_fronzoni-64-lounge-chair/fronzoni-lounge-chair-1.jpg?q=60"></div></figure>
<p>If you are unfamiliar with the work of A G Fronzoni, this is going to be a pretty good place to start. Undoubtedly one of history’s greatest designers and teachers, Fronzoni was known for his work in graphic design, publishing, industrial design, architecture, and design education. He opened two studios in his lifetime. He spent much of his career educating others while working as a Professor at various design schools during the 1970s. He later opened his own school in 1982, La ScuolaBottega. His industrial design work includes the Quadra Lamp, designed in 1963, the Form Zero 63+65 suitcase series for Valextra, as well as the Series ’64 furniture line, which is still in production today with <a href="https://www.cappellini.com/en/designer/agfronzoni" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Cappellini</a>. And it is this ’64 line—specifically the Fronzoni lounge chair—that we celebrate a true beauty of minimalism in design.</p>
<figure class="img-figure"><div class="img-wrapper" data-orientation="landscape" style="padding-bottom: 66.6%"><img alt="Fronzoni 64 Lounge Chair" class="img" data-original="100w" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 446px) 402px, (max-width: 600px) 504px, 702px" src="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/183_fronzoni-64-lounge-chair/fronzoni-lounge-chair-2.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60" srcset="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/183_fronzoni-64-lounge-chair/fronzoni-lounge-chair-2.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60 402w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/183_fronzoni-64-lounge-chair/fronzoni-lounge-chair-2.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60 504w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/183_fronzoni-64-lounge-chair/fronzoni-lounge-chair-2.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60 702w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/183_fronzoni-64-lounge-chair/fronzoni-lounge-chair-2.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 804w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/183_fronzoni-64-lounge-chair/fronzoni-lounge-chair-2.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1008w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/183_fronzoni-64-lounge-chair/fronzoni-lounge-chair-2.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1404w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/183_fronzoni-64-lounge-chair/fronzoni-lounge-chair-2.jpg?q=60"></div></figure>
<figure class="img-figure"><div class="img-wrapper" data-orientation="landscape" style="padding-bottom: 66.666666666667%"><img alt="Fronzoni 64 Lounge Chair" class="img" data-original="100w" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 446px) 402px, (max-width: 600px) 504px, 702px" src="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/183_fronzoni-64-lounge-chair/fronzoni-lounge-chair-5.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60" srcset="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/183_fronzoni-64-lounge-chair/fronzoni-lounge-chair-5.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60 402w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/183_fronzoni-64-lounge-chair/fronzoni-lounge-chair-5.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60 504w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/183_fronzoni-64-lounge-chair/fronzoni-lounge-chair-5.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60 702w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/183_fronzoni-64-lounge-chair/fronzoni-lounge-chair-5.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 804w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/183_fronzoni-64-lounge-chair/fronzoni-lounge-chair-5.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1008w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/183_fronzoni-64-lounge-chair/fronzoni-lounge-chair-5.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1404w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/183_fronzoni-64-lounge-chair/fronzoni-lounge-chair-5.jpg?q=60"></div></figure>
<p>With its distinctive thin clean lines, the Fron­zoni ​’64 lounge chair features a recti­lin­ear frame in squared tubular steel. Discreet, under­side slats support a thin profile seat cushion expanse in polyurethane foam with two removable recti­lin­ear squared bolsters that func­tion as back­rest cush­ions. The lounge chair is avail­able with a choice or black or white matte lacquer frame as well as black or white uphol­stery in a choice of leather or synthetic leather as well as a select cotton fabric.</p>
<p>Fronzoni’s work was deeply influ­enced by both Mies van der Rohe’s and Marcel Breuer’s philoso­phies of synthe­sis and subtrac­tion and is evident in his mini­mal­ist ​’64 Collec­tion designed in 1964 for Cappellini that included a coffee table, dining tables of various sizes, a dining chair, a lounge chair, and even beds of varying sizes. Fron­zoni used squared tubular steel to render recti­lin­ear shapes that func­tion as the outlines of his furni­ture, defin­ing planes of space. These slim profile outlines create an exquis­ite geomet­ri­cal expres­sion and levity within the forms, and their respec­tive support struc­tures allow the viewer to liter­ally see through them.</p>
<figure class="img-figure"><div class="img-wrapper" data-orientation="landscape" style="padding-bottom: 66.666666666667%"><img alt="Fronzoni 64 Lounge Chair" class="img" data-original="100w" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 446px) 402px, (max-width: 600px) 504px, 702px" src="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/183_fronzoni-64-lounge-chair/fronzoni-lounge-chair-3.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60" srcset="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/183_fronzoni-64-lounge-chair/fronzoni-lounge-chair-3.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60 402w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/183_fronzoni-64-lounge-chair/fronzoni-lounge-chair-3.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60 504w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/183_fronzoni-64-lounge-chair/fronzoni-lounge-chair-3.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60 702w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/183_fronzoni-64-lounge-chair/fronzoni-lounge-chair-3.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 804w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/183_fronzoni-64-lounge-chair/fronzoni-lounge-chair-3.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1008w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/183_fronzoni-64-lounge-chair/fronzoni-lounge-chair-3.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1404w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/183_fronzoni-64-lounge-chair/fronzoni-lounge-chair-3.jpg?q=60"></div></figure>
<figure class="img-figure"><div class="img-wrapper" data-orientation="landscape" style="padding-bottom: 66.666666666667%"><img alt="Fronzoni 64 Lounge Chair" class="img" data-original="100w" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 446px) 402px, (max-width: 600px) 504px, 702px" src="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/183_fronzoni-64-lounge-chair/fronzoni-lounge-chair-6.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60" srcset="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/183_fronzoni-64-lounge-chair/fronzoni-lounge-chair-6.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60 402w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/183_fronzoni-64-lounge-chair/fronzoni-lounge-chair-6.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60 504w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/183_fronzoni-64-lounge-chair/fronzoni-lounge-chair-6.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60 702w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/183_fronzoni-64-lounge-chair/fronzoni-lounge-chair-6.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 804w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/183_fronzoni-64-lounge-chair/fronzoni-lounge-chair-6.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1008w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/183_fronzoni-64-lounge-chair/fronzoni-lounge-chair-6.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1404w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/183_fronzoni-64-lounge-chair/fronzoni-lounge-chair-6.jpg?q=60"></div></figure>
<figure class="img-figure"><div class="img-wrapper" data-orientation="landscape" style="padding-bottom: 66.666666666667%"><img alt="Fronzoni 64 Lounge Chair" class="img" data-original="100w" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 446px) 402px, (max-width: 600px) 504px, 702px" src="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/183_fronzoni-64-lounge-chair/fronzoni-lounge-chair-4.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60" srcset="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/183_fronzoni-64-lounge-chair/fronzoni-lounge-chair-4.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60 402w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/183_fronzoni-64-lounge-chair/fronzoni-lounge-chair-4.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60 504w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/183_fronzoni-64-lounge-chair/fronzoni-lounge-chair-4.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60 702w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/183_fronzoni-64-lounge-chair/fronzoni-lounge-chair-4.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 804w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/183_fronzoni-64-lounge-chair/fronzoni-lounge-chair-4.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1008w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/183_fronzoni-64-lounge-chair/fronzoni-lounge-chair-4.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1404w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/183_fronzoni-64-lounge-chair/fronzoni-lounge-chair-4.jpg?q=60"></div></figure>
<p>You can discover more about the Italian master through Ester Manitto’s book, <em><a href="https://minimalissimo.shop/product/a-lesson-with-a-g-fronzoni" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">A Lesson with A G Fronzoni</a></em>. This book is an act of gratitude from student to teacher and also an invitation to others to contribute to the reconstruction of a story of human and professional experience of the highest value and of great current relevance. Ester Manitto, re-working the materials, notes, and written work of her student career permits us to enter the world of A G Fronzoni’s workshop school, founded in Milan in 1982 and active until 2001.</p>
<figure class="img-figure"><div class="img-wrapper" data-orientation="square" style="padding-bottom: 100%"><img alt="A Lesson with A G Fronzoni" class="img" data-original="100w" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 446px) 402px, (max-width: 600px) 336px , 468px" src="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/183_fronzoni-64-lounge-chair/artivadesign-01-q85.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60" srcset="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/183_fronzoni-64-lounge-chair/artivadesign-01-q85.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60 402w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/183_fronzoni-64-lounge-chair/artivadesign-01-q85.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60 504w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/183_fronzoni-64-lounge-chair/artivadesign-01-q85.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60 702w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/183_fronzoni-64-lounge-chair/artivadesign-01-q85.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 804w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/183_fronzoni-64-lounge-chair/artivadesign-01-q85.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1008w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/183_fronzoni-64-lounge-chair/artivadesign-01-q85.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1404w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/183_fronzoni-64-lounge-chair/artivadesign-01-q85.jpg?q=60"></div></figure>
<figure class="img-figure"><div class="img-wrapper" data-orientation="square" style="padding-bottom: 100%"><img alt="A Lesson with A G Fronzoni" class="img" data-original="100w" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 446px) 402px, (max-width: 600px) 336px , 468px" src="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/183_fronzoni-64-lounge-chair/artivadesign-06-q85.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60" srcset="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/183_fronzoni-64-lounge-chair/artivadesign-06-q85.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60 402w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/183_fronzoni-64-lounge-chair/artivadesign-06-q85.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60 504w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/183_fronzoni-64-lounge-chair/artivadesign-06-q85.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60 702w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/183_fronzoni-64-lounge-chair/artivadesign-06-q85.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 804w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/183_fronzoni-64-lounge-chair/artivadesign-06-q85.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1008w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/183_fronzoni-64-lounge-chair/artivadesign-06-q85.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1404w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/183_fronzoni-64-lounge-chair/artivadesign-06-q85.jpg?q=60"></div></figure>]]></description>
    </item>
        <item>
      <title>Materialising Silence</title>
      <link>https://minimalissimo.com/moods/materialising-silence</link>
      <guid>moods/materialising-silence</guid>
      <pubDate>Thu, 16 Jul 2020 00:00:00 +0200</pubDate>
      <description><![CDATA[<p>Interiors designed like a temple dedicated to the contemplation and spirituality. Timeless simplicity and elegance are expressed through an architecture based on a particular choice of material and a wise use of light. Silence invites spirituality in this house surrounded by nature projected by <a href="http://www.giorgioravastudio.it/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Giorgio Rava Studio</a>.</p><img alt="" src="https://minimalissimo.com/content/moods/64_materialising-silence/giorgioravastudio_hillsresidence_3.jpg"><img alt="" src="https://minimalissimo.com/content/moods/64_materialising-silence/giorgioravastudio_hillsresidence_6.jpg"><img alt="" src="https://minimalissimo.com/content/moods/64_materialising-silence/giorgioravastudio_hillsresidence_11.jpg"><img alt="" src="https://minimalissimo.com/content/moods/64_materialising-silence/infinito-1b_3.jpg"><img alt="" src="https://minimalissimo.com/content/moods/64_materialising-silence/infinito-2.jpg"><img alt="" src="https://minimalissimo.com/content/moods/64_materialising-silence/infinito-5.jpg"><img alt="" src="https://minimalissimo.com/content/moods/64_materialising-silence/infinito-7.jpg"><img alt="" src="https://minimalissimo.com/content/moods/64_materialising-silence/infinito-9b.jpg">]]></description>
    </item>
        <item>
      <title>Torino Outlet Village</title>
      <link>https://minimalissimo.com/articles/torino-outlet-village</link>
      <guid>articles/torino-outlet-village</guid>
      <pubDate>Wed, 15 Jul 2020 00:00:00 +0200</pubDate>
      <description><![CDATA[<figure class="img-figure"><div class="img-wrapper" data-orientation="portrait" style="padding-bottom: 150%"><img alt="Torino Outlet Village by Claudio Silvestrin" class="img" data-original="100w" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 446px) 402px, (max-width: 600px) 336px , 468px" src="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/182_torino-outlet-village/torino-outlet-village-7.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60" srcset="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/182_torino-outlet-village/torino-outlet-village-7.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60 402w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/182_torino-outlet-village/torino-outlet-village-7.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60 504w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/182_torino-outlet-village/torino-outlet-village-7.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60 702w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/182_torino-outlet-village/torino-outlet-village-7.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 804w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/182_torino-outlet-village/torino-outlet-village-7.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1008w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/182_torino-outlet-village/torino-outlet-village-7.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1404w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/182_torino-outlet-village/torino-outlet-village-7.jpg?q=60"></div></figure>
<p>Architecture is a public good, and therefore it follows that architecture should serve the public. Often, especially in minimalism, great design is reserved for private dwellings. This is not the case with <a href="https://www.claudiosilvestrin.com/portfolio/torino-outlet-village/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Torino Outlet Village</a> by the renowned <a href="https://www.claudiosilvestrin.com/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Claudio Silvestrin</a>, who once studied under the master designer and teacher <a href="https://minimalissimo.shop/product/a-lesson-with-a-g-fronzoni" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">A G Fronzoni</a>. Located outside of Turin, Italy, this stunning shopping plaza is a unique piece of architecture enjoyed by all who visit.</p>
<figure class="img-figure"><div class="img-wrapper" data-orientation="square" style="padding-bottom: 100%"><img alt="Torino Outlet Village by Claudio Silvestrin" class="img" data-original="100w" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 446px) 402px, (max-width: 600px) 336px , 468px" src="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/182_torino-outlet-village/torino-outlet-village-6.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60" srcset="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/182_torino-outlet-village/torino-outlet-village-6.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60 402w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/182_torino-outlet-village/torino-outlet-village-6.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60 504w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/182_torino-outlet-village/torino-outlet-village-6.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60 702w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/182_torino-outlet-village/torino-outlet-village-6.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 804w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/182_torino-outlet-village/torino-outlet-village-6.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1008w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/182_torino-outlet-village/torino-outlet-village-6.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1404w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/182_torino-outlet-village/torino-outlet-village-6.jpg?q=60"></div></figure>
<figure class="img-figure"><div class="img-wrapper" data-orientation="portrait" style="padding-bottom: 150%"><img alt="Torino Outlet Village by Claudio Silvestrin" class="img" data-original="100w" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 446px) 402px, (max-width: 600px) 336px , 468px" src="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/182_torino-outlet-village/torino-outlet-village-3.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60" srcset="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/182_torino-outlet-village/torino-outlet-village-3.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60 402w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/182_torino-outlet-village/torino-outlet-village-3.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60 504w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/182_torino-outlet-village/torino-outlet-village-3.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60 702w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/182_torino-outlet-village/torino-outlet-village-3.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 804w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/182_torino-outlet-village/torino-outlet-village-3.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1008w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/182_torino-outlet-village/torino-outlet-village-3.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1404w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/182_torino-outlet-village/torino-outlet-village-3.jpg?q=60"></div></figure>
<p>Visible from the highway below, the open-air Torino Outlet Village is comprised of many shops bordering a long promenade. The defining feature is the 88 metre high spire, which rises from above the shops and visitors and beneath it. The spire is as symbolic as it is practical: not only does it serve as an easily recognisable landmark, but is also a figurative bridge between earth and sky. The spire shoots up to the sky in an unparalleled design—an instant icon.</p>
<figure class="img-figure"><div class="img-wrapper" data-orientation="portrait" style="padding-bottom: 149.91666666667%"><img alt="Torino Outlet Village by Claudio Silvestrin" class="img" data-original="100w" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 446px) 402px, (max-width: 600px) 336px , 468px" src="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/182_torino-outlet-village/torino-outlet-village-2.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60" srcset="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/182_torino-outlet-village/torino-outlet-village-2.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60 402w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/182_torino-outlet-village/torino-outlet-village-2.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60 504w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/182_torino-outlet-village/torino-outlet-village-2.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60 702w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/182_torino-outlet-village/torino-outlet-village-2.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 804w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/182_torino-outlet-village/torino-outlet-village-2.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1008w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/182_torino-outlet-village/torino-outlet-village-2.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1404w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/182_torino-outlet-village/torino-outlet-village-2.jpg?q=60"></div></figure>
<figure class="img-figure"><div class="img-wrapper" data-orientation="landscape" style="padding-bottom: 66.583333333333%"><img alt="Torino Outlet Village by Claudio Silvestrin" class="img" data-original="100w" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 446px) 402px, (max-width: 600px) 504px, 702px" src="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/182_torino-outlet-village/torino-outlet-village-9.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60" srcset="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/182_torino-outlet-village/torino-outlet-village-9.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60 402w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/182_torino-outlet-village/torino-outlet-village-9.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60 504w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/182_torino-outlet-village/torino-outlet-village-9.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60 702w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/182_torino-outlet-village/torino-outlet-village-9.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 804w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/182_torino-outlet-village/torino-outlet-village-9.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1008w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/182_torino-outlet-village/torino-outlet-village-9.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1404w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/182_torino-outlet-village/torino-outlet-village-9.jpg?q=60"></div></figure>
<p>Visitors to the plaza enter through a gate nestled underneath the impressive spire. The rows of storefronts spread in long lines in front of the viewer, bordering a wide walkway. Opposite the tower sits a reflecting pool. The body of water is housed in an infinity pool so well structured that one can hardly tell where the pond ends and the buildings begin. Further accentuating the monumental feel of the space, identical trees line both sides of the plaza. The trees, combined with the open-air concept, invite one to linger and enjoy the outdoors.</p>
<figure class="img-figure"><div class="img-wrapper" data-orientation="portrait" style="padding-bottom: 149.91666666667%"><img alt="Torino Outlet Village by Claudio Silvestrin" class="img" data-original="100w" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 446px) 402px, (max-width: 600px) 336px , 468px" src="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/182_torino-outlet-village/torino-outlet-village-1.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60" srcset="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/182_torino-outlet-village/torino-outlet-village-1.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60 402w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/182_torino-outlet-village/torino-outlet-village-1.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60 504w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/182_torino-outlet-village/torino-outlet-village-1.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60 702w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/182_torino-outlet-village/torino-outlet-village-1.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 804w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/182_torino-outlet-village/torino-outlet-village-1.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1008w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/182_torino-outlet-village/torino-outlet-village-1.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1404w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/182_torino-outlet-village/torino-outlet-village-1.jpg?q=60"></div></figure>
<figure class="img-figure"><div class="img-wrapper" data-orientation="landscape" style="padding-bottom: 66.666666666667%"><img alt="Torino Outlet Village by Claudio Silvestrin" class="img" data-original="100w" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 446px) 402px, (max-width: 600px) 504px, 702px" src="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/182_torino-outlet-village/torino-outlet-village-4.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60" srcset="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/182_torino-outlet-village/torino-outlet-village-4.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60 402w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/182_torino-outlet-village/torino-outlet-village-4.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60 504w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/182_torino-outlet-village/torino-outlet-village-4.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60 702w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/182_torino-outlet-village/torino-outlet-village-4.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 804w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/182_torino-outlet-village/torino-outlet-village-4.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1008w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/182_torino-outlet-village/torino-outlet-village-4.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1404w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/182_torino-outlet-village/torino-outlet-village-4.jpg?q=60"></div></figure>
<p>The unique design of the Outlet Village makes it hard to pinpoint the design in a specific time in architecture history. This is intentional, and a specialty of Silvestrin’s. Timeless and genre-defying designs abound in Silvestrin’s portfolio, not surprising given that he draws his inspiration from historical and contemporary sources. Torino Outlet Village is a pleasant mixture of traditional and modern elements. Ancient materials of stone and lime plaster cover the exterior facade. The large stone blocks that form the structure are a soft tan, reminiscent of earth and nature. This material is contrasted sharply with the smooth white of the tower, arguably one of the most recognisable modern elements in the region. The mix of classic and avant-garde design play together well, allowing the viewer to feel as if they are surrounded by the highest level of creativity. </p>
<figure class="img-figure"><div class="img-wrapper" data-orientation="landscape" style="padding-bottom: 66.583333333333%"><img alt="Torino Outlet Village by Claudio Silvestrin" class="img" data-original="100w" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 446px) 402px, (max-width: 600px) 504px, 702px" src="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/182_torino-outlet-village/torino-outlet-village-8.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60" srcset="https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/182_torino-outlet-village/torino-outlet-village-8.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60 402w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/182_torino-outlet-village/torino-outlet-village-8.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60 504w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/182_torino-outlet-village/torino-outlet-village-8.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60 702w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/182_torino-outlet-village/torino-outlet-village-8.jpg?w=402&amp;h=402&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 804w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/182_torino-outlet-village/torino-outlet-village-8.jpg?w=504&amp;h=504&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1008w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/182_torino-outlet-village/torino-outlet-village-8.jpg?w=702&amp;h=702&amp;q=60&amp;dpr=2 1404w,https://minimalissimo.imgix.net/content/articles/182_torino-outlet-village/torino-outlet-village-8.jpg?q=60"></div></figure>
