<p>Silvestrin takes pleasure in finding the complexity behind a seemingly simple design. There is always a richness behind simplicity, a story that is not visible on the surface. This concept is literal in the design of Torino Outlet Village, where the exterior facade hides the bustle of shops and customers. Yet there is also a philosophical richness: while the form of the structure may be simple, the meanings behind its design are abundant. According to Silvestrin, the design of the structure emphasises <em>visual clarity, freedom of movement, open perspectives, and visual order.</em></p>]]></description>
